Articles.Content:
I saw the launch from my back yard, and I didn't see any big clouds of smoke!

I managed to grab some screenshots of the telemetry screen from the ULA webcast on my phone. I have to say... KSP looks better!

There's another 3 hours before it does fires up the RL-10 again for the circularization burn - "The targeted circular orbit is 11,047 nautical miles with an inclination of 55 degrees."
